info.author: Stephen Mitchell
info.description:
publishstatic is a django management command that helps automate uploading static files to a server.  Used in conjunction with the ManifestStaticFilesStorage engine, it uploads only changed files to Amazon's S3 and Cloudfront servers.

After collecting static, run ./manange.py publishstatic.  Any changed files will be uploaded to the static file server.

info.name: publishstatic
info.summary: Django management command to upload changed static files.
info.html_description:
publishstatic is a django management command that helps automate uploading static files to a server. Used in conjunction with the ManifestStaticFilesStorage engine, it uploads only changed files to Amazon’s S3 and Cloudfront servers.

After collecting static, run ./manange.py publishstatic. Any changed files will be uploaded to the static file server.
